p: Whether you’re at Dante to drink a negroni via a porrón — the infamous Spanish drinking vessel — or to converse over a few afternoon spritzes’ with friends, Dante’s two West Village locations are a must-visit in New York City. Rated the world’s best bar in 2019, Dante is a modern-day icon in the bar world. There’s no reason why their website would be anything short of world-class. Dazzling photographs of craft cocktails across a minimalist design.
